{
  "texts": [
    " Organizations aiming for faster release cycles and improved software reliability should prioritize AI integration in their QA strategies.",
    "The infusion of Artificial Intelligence (AI) into software Quality Assurance (QA) represents a paradigm shift from traditional, script-based testing to intelligent, adaptive, and autonomous validation systems.",
    "However, despite its promise, the implementation of AI in QA is not without obstacles.",
    "This section provides a deepdive analysis of the tangible benefits and existing limitations of AI-driven QA, particularly focusing on test case design and test data generation.",
    "The evaluation draws upon practical experiences, industry data, and experimental results presented in earlier sections of this study."
  ]
}